{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# GraphFleet Quickstart\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook shows you how to quickly get started with GraphFleet. We'll cover:\n",
    "1. Project initialization\n",
    "2. Adding documents\n",
    "3. Creating indexes\n",
    "4. Basic querying"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "from graphfleet.core import GraphFleet\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize project\n",
    "project_dir = Path(\"./data\")\n",
    "GraphFleet.init_project(project_dir)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Add Documents\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's add some example documents to our project."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create example documents\n",
    "docs_dir = project_dir / \"raw\"\n",
    "docs_dir.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Write example document\n",
    "with open(docs_dir / \"example.txt\", \"w\") as f:\n",
    "    f.write(\"\"\"This is an example document about artificial intelligence.\n",
    "AI systems can now perform various tasks like natural language processing,\n",
    "computer vision, and decision making.\"\"\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Create Index\n",
    "\n",
    "Now let's create an index from our documents."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize GraphFleet\n",
    "graph_fleet = GraphFleet(project_dir)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create index\n",
    "graph_fleet.create_index()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Query the Index\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's try different types of queries."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Standard query\n",
    "result = graph_fleet.query(\"What tasks can AI systems perform?\")\n",
    "print(\"Standard Query Result:\")\n",
    "print(result)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Local query\n",
    "result = graph_fleet.query_local(\"Tell me about natural language processing\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nLocal Query Result:\")\n",
    "print(result)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Global query\n",
    "result = graph_fleet.query_global(\"What are the main capabilities of AI?\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nGlobal Query Result:\")\n",
    "print(result)"
   ]
  }
 ],
